CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Harbinger Of Spring - With the advent of balmy spring weather, Jean McClanahan of Webster Avenue turns her fancy to getting her lawn in shape. She'd make a good ad for garden implements, yes? - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jean McClanahan pushing wheelbarrow, next to three girls on porch clapping hands, 2900 block of Webster Avenue, Hill District
